caption: Food is very good, got veggie pad Thai and some Maki rolls, all were tasty and delivered meeting my expectations. No wait at all, food was done in 20min. I like this place because they have organic options compared to other restaurants, but maybe that's going away since I don't see that in there website like before.  They are intense about COVID. Barricaded doors with chairs. They drop food outside door and you pickup. Wouldn't let me go inside.

RUN AWAY!!!  The worst customer service I’ve ever experienced.  I placed a pick up order through door dash and when I arrived, the lady at the restaurant,through the glass window without opening the door, wrote on a piece of paper that they have nothing for me and said “bye-bye”.  When I tried to explain and get an answer, she just walked away.  Horrible experience.  I don’t need food from a place who treat their customers this way.  Thankfully, there is so much choice around. Never again!
Place just don't care about there customers
Daughter loves their snow mountain and pink lady maki.
Decent sushi place a little over priced got some friendly servers.
The lady answering the phone is extremely rude and unprofessional
I really liked their dishes. I always get awesome customer service there. The place is neat and the employees are always very welcoming. Will visit here again.

Ordered delivery and they sent me the wrong food. Called back to tell them and they said they could send replacement in an hour. My kids are already hungry so I said I am going to eat the incorrect sent food and they tell me that is fine. An hour later they call and say I need to give them back the incorrect sent food or they won't deliver what I ordered. Also told me I need to "respect the food".. Terrible customer service. On top of all that the sushi was extremely cold in the inside and tasted like it was still half frozen.

We loved dining here.  Very nice place be in, it's casual enough yet very nice and you are able to relax.  The food is very good.  We got sushi and some plated orders to share with the table.  Excellent vegetarian sushi choices.  We had the sweet potato rolls, avocado cucumber rolls, vegetable tempura rolls with nice dipping sauce and pickled ginger.  Also, lo mein, chicken fingers(very nice!) and scallion pancakes that I find to be be the best around, by far, and thise come with a terrific soy ginger sauce.  Everything was great and the place just has a special touch with care in choosing their ingredients where they can.  We dine in and get take out and it is always top notch, very glad to have it nearby.
Food was not ready till over an hour past pickup time. No attenp was made to warn me it would be late no discount or other attempts to make right offered. Order placed over an hour in advance

Eggrolls are pretty bad. For $4.50 for one eggroll it should be amazing. Orange chicken is good. Wonton soup isn't bad but a little different than typical. Pretty much everything is just okay but pricey
Horribly long wait
Had a great experience in here with my girlfriend. The food comes fast and the service is just excellent. Prices are fair.
They should show options for nori or soy wraps!  I never wanted soy wraps.  At least ½ the reason I get nori rolls is for the nori.

Placed an online order for pickup at 2pm since I had to drop something at a nearby shop. They called at 1:30pm just as I was leaving to tell me they'd finished the order early and I needed to pick it up now, didn't care about the scheduled time or that I was just now leaving the house.  When I got there I saw my order out on the front step, unwatched, in the middle of a torrential downpour. They also had the doors closed and blocked with chairs, and the lights off. I grabbed the damp bag, ran to do my errand, and headed home.  When I got home I realized they'd probably set the order out immediately after calling me, as the bag was also very wet on the inside and the food was completely cold. Also half was missing - not sure if they just never put it in, or if some hungry passerby helped themselves. Either way, just threw the rest out.  Yum.

Excellent food for delivery in Medford (and neighboring towns)!  Highly recommend chicken & broccoli, spare ribs, shumai, crab rangoon, avocado salad, sushi & General Gau’s chicken.  Many tasty gluten free options.

I ordered from Grubhub. The restaurant accepted the order and 1 hour after it was supposed to be delivered it was still not here. They did not pick up the phone. To make it worse Grubhub also is taking forever to give a credit. Will never use either company again.
I had high hopes but ended up with disappointment. The only good thing was the water and the candy.

We were a little skeptical based on some of the reviews but decided to try out this place before heading to see Jo Koy. The service was fast and the food was great. I only took off one start because I agree the laser lights are just strange and distracting ;)  Otherwise totally worth another try.
Amazing sushi especially for the price, staff was perfect and a comfortable environment, will be visiting again very soon.

First time.  It's not bad.  The service is pretty slow and the cooks were talking in the phone constantly but the fish was fresh and food is pretty good. It's better than prepackaged sushi, hopefully it was just an off-night

We came pretty late and it was still busy, but not packed. Service was not the best. When she brought out our appetizer, put it down and turned away, 2 minutes later she passes by and asked "did you not order that?"  We said we did except we don't have plates to eat it with. There were only 5 of us and they gave us a table big enough for 8-9 people, which we thought, great, more space. Except when food came, we all had a hard time reaching for food that weren't directly in front of us. The servers also couldn't reach us because all the dishes she brought out, she left it at one side of the edge, making it even harder for us to reach it. My suggestion is invest in a lazy Suzy.

Really good quality sushi creative chefs, friendly service small, casual place if you’re enjoying yourself with a good meal chefs are open to offer suggestions and come up with some really creative stuff that’s fun to try!
“Organic” pumping out farm raised salmon. Not great sushi
Never experienced dine-in service, but take out food was quite good.

Overall, it was just disappointing, and this does not seem to be an isolated opinion based upon the tables around us.  Our waiter (who seemed to be the only one working for the entire restaurant two hours before showtime for the nearby theater) had a hard time understanding customers when they ordered, forgot items, never returned to refill anyone’s water (even watched one gentleman stand up and retrieve the water pitcher from the waiter’s stand to fill his table’s glasses), cleared some of our dishes without even asking if we were finished and brought all of the food at once to many tables (apps, sushi, hot items all together).  The sushi was okay but nothing above three stars.  No cocktail menu and they were out of all but the cheapest sake on the menu.  And the laser lights dancing over the ceilings and walls that also shone onto patrons and into their eyes...  we won’t be back.
I ordered through Seamless, and 60 minutes later I got a notice that my order was cancelled. Ridiculous and unprofessional. Don't make promises you can't keep.
Suprisingly fantastic food.... You will love it.

Don’t ever try to order food online. They use Grabull, which is awful and has nobody answering phones & when you ask them to account for problems with online delivery they say it’s not their responsibility. I’m not writing this bad review because they forgot my duck sauce. My order never came and they told me there was nothing they could do for me even though I was charged.

Good food, HORRIFIC EXPERIENCE! I came here to celebrate my husbands birthday, on Tuesday,December 10th, 2019 at 5pm... the restaurant at this time was empty when my family and I came to eat. As we were ordering food our waitress was rushing our order to bring it to the kitchen, but the restaurant at this time was EMPTY and we were the only ones there; its a Tuesday night let me remind you... once the food came we asked for forks, our waitress brought one when there was 3 of us. When she brought 2 more forks, she THREW them on my mothers plate of food where she was eating!!... seriously.... absolutely not... As we kept making food requests she was not shy in hiding her face expressions that she was clearly upset about something... When we payed the bill , our waitress didn’t like our tip and she asked us if it was our first time in America... lol ... just wow...

We dined here before going to the Chevalier Theatre for "Ladies Night Out." Pleasant atmosphere and coat racks near the restrooms. Wait staff are cheerful and helpful. Serving portions are large and the food is good. We ordered sushi and Yoki Udon and were very satisfied with our choices. Will definitely return.
Had a fantastic experience in here with my daughter. The food was served quick and the service is just fantastic. Prices are convenient.
The waiter was very nice. The pink lady roll was superb

Food was pretty good, but service was all over the place. No communication from our server (legit didn't say any words just stood there with a pen) but then the manager helped. Got soup spilled on me (totally fine, mistakes happen) but he didn't even say sorry just started rubbing the soup off me.  Food was pretty standard and I'll chalk up the server to being new but maybe keep a more experienced person with him?
Do NOT order from there on grub hub. They're over 2 hours late and when I called they say "we're getting ready for dinner busy and the computers broken" even tho it's noon 12 o'clock.

The restaurant was a hit & miss with me. The place itself was very nice & cozy & inviting, & everything looked really nice inside. The food was good & taste wise it was just right. The noodle soup was delicious as well as  the shrimp tempura. Service was strange to say the least as this was my first time there trying to read through their extensive menu & I felt rushed to make a decision, & there was nobody there. I didn’t even have time to finish my appetizer when the main course was already coming felt so fast & my apps were getting cold. In the end the food was good but overall experience was sub par.
Often have issues with delivery and sometimes pickup. If you order on a Friday night, it will take an hour and sometimes they lose your order. BUT everything we've had is very good.

I order from this establishment because they have a gluten free menu. Twice I’ve had delivery orders take over an hour and half to be delivered even though the confirmation email says 45-60 min. The food is definitely not worth the wait!!

We have been here 8-10 times and it is usually pretty good, nothing spectacular, but it the best sushi in Medford for what that is worth.  On our recent visit however we waited 10 minutes and the waiters brought food to the nearby tables, got them their check, went back and took their money, returned and gave them change, and then disappeared.  They never said a word to us.  It wasn't even very busy, we were the fifth table I think.  We got up and left.  I am not going to reward poor service.  Get your act together.  It isn't hard to get customers a beer or Coke while they wait.  Let me order some miso soup.  At least I would be trapped at that point, having drank your beer, and you could then ignore me over the next two hours and I couldn't leave.

A very cozy place in Medford on a street corner that you'd miss if you weren't looking for it. I was immediately greeted and sat at the bar to watch the chefs. I ordered the House Hot Sake which came out at the perfect temp and taste. I was then given a complimentary order of what seemed like an orange pickeled cabbage with slices of avocado. Very tasty! I then  ordered the Sashimi Sushi Combo with a side order of sashimi octopus. The octopus was the freshest I've ever had and were thick slices. The rest of the meal was expertly prepared with attention to the presentation. Sashimi was again cut thick and melted in my mouth. The sushi was a crunchy roll that had a great blend of tastes. The whole meal was the perfect amount of food for a hungry person. I ended with a Sapporo beer and thanked the chefs for a wonderful dinner. I would highly suggest to have dinner here if you love sashimi! I'll be back!
Top taste in my opinion.  The boneless spareribs are unsurpassed. Pork lomein also better than my (former) regular place.  Sushi as good as anyplace around.  I will return because of food quality.
Classic Japanese sushi in downtown Medford.
Great service, affordable prices and good sushi
Nice casual place for couple or friend get together. Good selection of shushi and other Japanese foods.

My first time and last time! I ordered fried chicken and fried plantains But unfortunately I didn’t get my plantains and also the chicken had an horrible smell same for some kind of sauce you guys put on the side It looks like the food is poisoned
Have tried it before , didn’t like their food. And the sushi was really bad. Not fresh at all, I wouldn’t call them sushi master.
Sushi bar was delicious
Excellent quality and taste, friendly and efficient service.

Good food at decent prices! Our table ordered shumai, gyoza, and maki roll lunch specials. Everything was beautifully plated, and flavors were good. Knocked down a couple of stars because service was pretty terrible... Hadn't been back here for a few years and probably won't go back, at least not for a late lunch.

Ordered through GrubHub - they wouldn't cancel the order but wouldn't deliver it. I called after they were over 20 minutes late, and they said "we want to cancel it." When I called GrubHub, they said it wasn't cancelled, but it appeared they weren't even going to attempt to fulfill it. This was all one hour and fifteen minutes after my order. Completely ridiculous!
I will have go back to enjoy myself again!

Went here before a big event in Medford. Staff was clearly overwhelmed. Instead of getting some back up from the kitchen or management there was only one poor waitress trying to ferry the food and take orders for the whole restaurant. I have been on quieter nights and the service was always fine. This night was an exception. Just can't understand how someone from the back did not come out and help the one waitress though. The sushi is fantastic however. Order out or done in on a quiet night. Yummy.
Great atmosphere and food
The food was ok. The service was terrible.  Took an hour to get the check.
Best place for sushi. Took my lady here and she fell in love. So many to choose from.

Love this place!!  Their sushi is delicious. They have great food, great service and wonderful staff. Thank you for all you do. I wish more places had the business integrity, selection, and qualityBlue Fuji.
I really liked the mango California, sweet potato and New England maki rolls. They have a lot of different special rolls that it makes it tough to choose just a few. I'll be back to try more!

Ordered two lunch specials for pick up. When picking up noticed the bag looked unusually small. Asked the main lady if there were miso soups in the bag, she said yes. Got home, no soups in the bag. The sushi was decent but there are better places around. That sort of mix up even after specifically checking has kind of turned me off from going back.
Perfection right there
The gluten free options are okay, not completely sure it is safe for celiacs.

Blue Fuji's food was phenomenal.  We loved our food. Our only criticism was that the appetizers and entrees were brought at the same time. Service was very good; portions were large, and the atmosphere was very nice. Our dishes included mushroom soup,  hot and sour soup, scallion pie, shrimp and vegetable tempura, shrimp and broccoli,  spicy green beans and jasmine rice.

2 hour delivery, was told 45 min. Ordered delivery at 6:30pm, didn't end up receiving it until 8:30pm. When I called and finally reached a person to talk to, she said they had received about 200 delivery orders for only 3 drivers. Additionally, when we finally got our food it turned out that they entered in wrong item, and we were charged for the item we wanted which was more expensive. Line so busy that cannot even call to complain or give them opportunity to fix order.
Atmosphere is awesome, staff is hella friendly, and any food I've had is next level delicious
Awesome sushi, great drinks. Organic and Gluten free options too!

The food was delicious.  The service was very sub-par.  There was only one person staffed in the front-of-house and that person was responsible for being hostess, inputting online orders to the system, and performing waitress duties for the entire restaurant.  Given the volume of online orders we witnessed, it was clear that one person is not enough to handle the load.  To make it worse, it was clear that the priority was processing of the online orders rather than making the in-restaurant experience enjoyable.  We waited 12 minutes to be seated (while watching online orders be input), watched and waited as our prepared rolls sat idle for at least 5 minutes at the sushi bar, and didn't receive our drink order until after the main course came.  Maybe there was a circumstance on this day that we are not aware of which resulted in the restaurant being understaffed, but if it's standard practice to have only one person on staff then I would not recommend dining in here.
Horrible!! Food was 3 hours late! Will NEVER order again!

The food here is overall just great quality. Everything tasted really fresh and you could tell the ingredients were high quality. We just moved to the area and wanted to find a good sushi place close by with delivery and this place is definitely going to be our go to spot from now on. Definitely recommend the Peking ravioli and sashimi!
Great food and service!

We have gone to some really good sushi places but never one I can actually walk to!!  This place is great!  Have had the sushi several times and is always fresh.  I have not, however, had the Chinese menu  which they also offer.  A definite try!
Ordered through Grabull. Arrived well before the quoted time which was appreciated.  I was a jerk and needed change for a twenty and the delivery guy was super gracious about it. Thank you!

The food here is overall just great quality. Everything tasted really fresh and you could tell the ingredients were high quality. We just moved to the area and wanted to find a good sushi place close by with delivery and this place is definitely going to be our go to spot from now on. Definitely recommend the Peking ravioli and sashimi!
Yummy dinner tonight .. my first time here and I will be back .. cannot wait to try rolls

We have gone to some really good sushi places but never one I can actually walk to!!  This place is great!  Have had the sushi several times and is always fresh.  I have not, however, had the Chinese menu  which they also offer.  A definite try!

I got the General Gao's chicken which advertises its chicken as organic.  While it was organic or not I couldn't really tell you but I enjoyed it a lot since they didn't really on heavy thick batter and sauce.  The thin batter and large chunks of chicken made for a very filling meal that didn't make me feel terrible after consuming which was surprising.

The restaurant has delicious food, excellent and friendly service and great ambiance.  The sushi is fresh as can be and the food overall, is cooked with care.  The chef will even send out new things for you to try to see what the response will be.  You feel good after eating here and I wish them well.

We've ordered (organic) sushi and pad thai through Grabull delivery service. Really appreciate the gluten free options. The food is always very tasty and tastes very flavorful and fresh, although sometimes the sushi rolls fall apart. Menu has some very creative combinations that I haven't tried before. Tried their other location in Bedford as well for lunch and catering, and both have been good.  The delivery has been on time and friendly.
Serves is on 100,and the food 8s top notch. The prices match this though.

What a nice place to go and enjoy lunch, they are kind loving and ready to make your meal with love! Take a minute to explore what a restaurant and customer service is all about. The waiter even assisted me right to my car with helping my friend who is in a wheelchair. Thank you for a great experience!
Sushi is so amazing i love this place for sushi
Ordered several rolls. Most were too heavy on the sauces to taste any other ingredients.
Rainy cold night but they were open till eleven. Asian comfort food just right.
Always great food and service
Sushi was ok. Poor service

The food was great, tasted very fresh and not greasy. The service was great when we first got there but I'm guessing the night got busy with delivery orders. After we ate they sort of forgot about us, odd as we were sitting in the middle of the small dining room. We waited 45 minutes for our bill, bedore finally getting up and asking for it. Would rate higher if not for this.
Good food
nice set maki!

30 minutes after they said it would be done. Ordered at 7:40 currently 9:20 food has not come. We ordered out before and it is typically quicker. This has happened before and we just left. Good food but takes a long time to come.
Impressive selection of sushi and sashimi. All with great presentation
sushi was fresh and delicious! I'll go again.
Great service - sushi was amazing

I ordered tonight and never got my meal. Meal was supposed to be delivered between 8:35pm to 8:45pm. By 9:40pm, we still never received our food. We called Grub Hub to cancel order. Went to BK to grab quick food and came back bc it was nearly 10pm. The delivery just came at 10pm as we were walking in from BK. When I called the restaurant at 8:50pm to check status of delivery, the gentleman I had talked to at the restaurant said 30 minutes. Delivery almost 1 hr and half later. Never, Never again
Waited two hours for delivery and cancelled the order. Got zero explanation other than they were busy on a Thursday night. Won't be ordering from here again.
The most gourmet, and traditional Asian food you'll find, yummy
Loved it
Good food and portions, best crab dragons I've ever eaten.
For a small inconspicuous spot, the food was excellent!  I don't do sushi, but the house rice, spareribs, crab rangoon- delicious!  I doubt they deliver to Everett, tho.
Great food for not a bad price! Really nice vibe inside
Good food. Could be better
Good food, nice quiet restaurant , good lighting... fresh hot meal. Very attentive service.
Food was good, service was ok. They're sushi isn't the greatest around
Diversity of the menu was off the charts

Blue Fuji is a staple at our house. My wife and I are both vegetarians and they're selection is spectacular. The service always comes with a cheery smile and they all seem to deeply enjoy their jobs. The interior asthetic is also very clean and brightly colored. If you haven't tried the Blue Fuji, you should.
Small restaurant with great sushi and Japanese entrees
Great food!
Excellent Asian. Sushi, yaki soba, teriyaki, all excellent. Will go again!
Nice atmosphere but the service was slow and the sushi was pretty strange - I didn't love it.
Solid. Value for money.

Excellent sushi and great service. We came in at 8:00 on a Wednesday (they were open til 10:00 or we would not have stopped) and the staff was courteous and attentive despite the fact we were the only patrons. It was clear they had been busy that night from the number of tables yet to be cleared or set, yet they were friendly and made us feel welcome. Good experience all around.
Nice little spot for sushi. Had a few rolls, sushi, and sashimi. Everything was very fresh and tasty. Service was quick too.
Delicious food and great atmosphere
Slow service

This was my first order with Blue Fuji and it will not be my last. I got a little of everything, Maki, steamed dumplings, rice, orange chicken and all it is so good. They delivered it at the exact time the online order said it would be here and the driver was so nice and friendly. Believe all the good reviews because they're true.
So good! We tried many rolls..scallops..shrimp..crab..tuna..all AMAZING! Service is friendly and fast!!

We eat at Blue Fuji regularly and like their sushi. Today we waited over an hour for our food to be delivered. When we called the restaurant we were told first that they couldn’t reach the driver. When they called back, they said he was “on his way” again.  They made no proposal of compensating us in any way. Very disappointing. Our hot food arrived cold. There are many sushi options in the area and we will look into discovering them. :(

For the second time, my partner and I placed a pickup order online through the website, got a confirmation email, and when we got to the restaurant, were told the order didn't go through. They said it "happens sometimes" and could place an order right then if we wanted. They didn't offer any other sort of assistance/discount/compensation. The staffer we were talking to said he wasn't authorized to do anything about it, and said the manager wasn't at the restaurant (on a Saturday evening!).  We left and grabbed the same items at Nagoya, a new place just around the corner. Highly recommended Nagoya!  I've had food from Blue Fuji before and it's fine, but avoid the hassle of dealing with them.
Everything is always good here

The Best over all Ethnic food i ever ate and the People there were have the nicest personality we ever seen in any Restraunt we ever been to and im 56yrs. Old. They are the BEST you will find plus the FOOD was so DELICIOUS, you all must atleast try it. Organic and Regular. THE BEST EVER.
Great organic Japanese and Chinese food.

Some of the most terrible service I have ever experienced at a restaurant. The first time I went with my partner, we sat at the table for about half an hour before a server even acknowledged us. Normally, the first question you are asked is what you would like to drink, but the server went straight to asking (rather impatiently) if we were ready to order yet.  The food was actually pretty good, but it took much longer than expected to arrive. Instead of asking about desserts, etc.,  we were abruptly given a bill and feeling incredibly rushed to leave.  We decided to try it again a few months later, hoping that perhaps they were just off their game that night. We walked in and we're completely ignored by the hoses. After waiting about 15 minutes, we just went to the bar and asked to be seated. The bartender seemed to be looking for a table, but never came back to follow up. After bring ignored by the hostess for yet another 15 minutes, we decided that the food, while good, was not special enough to tolerate the complete lack of professional service this place provides.  If you like to be ignored, rushed, and average food, this is your joint. However, if you like fast, friendly service, reasonable prices, and good food, check out some of their competition in Medford Square.
The New Wave Maki was fantastic.  Gyoza was also very good.  Great vegetarian options also.  The sushi boat ( we didn't order it but did see it at another table) looked great.
Food is excellent and fresh.  Prices are a little higher than the average place but you get it back in quality food.
Choice another place if you can!
Amazing mix of organic Chinese and Japanese cuisine.
The wait staff is very friendly and courteous.The food was excellent, it came out fast and it was hot..I recommend it highly.
(Translated by Google) Nice environment, house fried rice is delicious!  (Original) 环境不错，house炒饭很好吃！
Beautiful presentation and the sushi, delicious. Dim lights perfect for dinner time.
The food is good but a bit pricy. The service was poor when we went but since I've only gone once, I cannot say if it is a common occourance.
The food is fresh and flavorful-they accommodate my dietary restrictions. Julie is very kind and professional

Best place I bumped into, and can't stop going there now. Fresh food every single time, service is excellent and it's a feel at home environment. I definitely recommend this place, did I mention I live 45 minutes away? yeah it's that yummy👍👍

Called up 15 mins ahead and set up a table for us - nice! Service is like you want it - quick and prompt. Food is delicious, we tried quite a few things besides dessert and everything was on point, crab salad and house avocado salad was unreal!
Food was great, the staff was kind and attentive. They even accommodated a reservation for 12. Can't ask for much more!
very expensive and not very good. I would not order from this place again. I like good food.

Sat at the sushi bar and was treated to a great show and the best sushi I have ever had. The chefs were engaging and extremely talented,. Dinner was so good I came back the next day. Everytime I return to the Boston area I will stop in again.
Upper scale sushi hidden jewel
Great organic sushi and maki in Medford Square

Absolutely loved everything we ordered! The Blue Fuji roll was by far the best roll. The spicy tuna was in fact spicy, and the scallop shell appetizer was satisfying. This casual and cozy place will be our new go to for sushi!
Probably the best sushi/Chinese in medford. Convenient location downtown. Servers are friendly. Meals are a bit more expensive then the corner Chinese restaurant but well worth it.
We went for lunch on a Saturday. Terrible service, got a new waitperson with no experience and the manager ignored the problems.
Good food for the price
They have a great selection of sushi. The best part is the majority of items being organic. The quality in food and taste is noticed right away compared to other places.

Came here after evacuating from a nearby place. Though the owners are probably Chinese, the sushi and Western dessert was quite, quite good (definitely for Massachusetts). Also, my father being the traditional Chinese dad ordered 牛河粉 (beef chow foon), and it surprisingly was one of the best I've ever eaten. Not sure why this place never popped up when searching in a large area on maps.

Fun presentation, but the quality was okay at best.  A lot of their platters come with fried rolls, which is very heavy and greasy.  Some of the raw fish we ordered was still frozen.  Service was terrible.  We ordered multiple entrees for the table, but everything came out separately so we were left waiting in between entrees (luckily we were sharing, so no one was left without being able to eat).

Really nice atmosphere, very nicely lit (warm, comfy lighting). The quality of sushi was amazing. It's a bit pricier than other sushi in the area, but worth it. ($9-18 per roll) They have a much larger variety of sushi than other places, but that's also their biggest focus. There's no dessert. A great place for a date.
Sushi fish and rice are both very mediocre for their price. Makis are quite nice though, but still a bit on the expensive side.
Great Sushi!  Blue Fuji prides themselves in only providing organic foods

Wow, amazing food! The interior decor was beautiful and the atmosphere was nice (quiet, calm, not too full but also not deserted). We ordered a sushi roll and it was very soft, looked very pretty, and delicious. They have a lot of very different varieties of sushi in addition to the traditional flavors. I also ordered some house fried rice, which was amazing as well, and the teriyaki chicken was great.
Nice spot for dine in or take-out, friendly staff.
Excellent food
(Translated by Google) Fusion sushi.  (Original) Fusion sushi.
One of the best sushi places i had in a while. The only thing I can complain about is there drink menu. They had no mix drinks, just asian beer.
Never answer the phone mailbox I was full when you order took out do not recommend it

I have been to Blue Fuji Boston on several occasions. I was very impressed with the cleanliness of their restaurant and their friendly atmosphere. The Manager Julie even offered me a 10% discount on my bill! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!

Hands down the best sushi in the area. The have such a wide variety of rolls that use organic ingredients. They use mango instead of cucumber in many of their rolls, and it give it the same crunch with a nice kick of flavor. Try the Mango Boston roll, or the Spicy Avo crabmeat roll.

I was just overcharged for a delivery order and was given a website to send a screenshot of the online menu with false pricing?!? Unacceptable. I will never order from you people again. Oh, and I sent the screenshot. Beware people!!
Beautiful, modern and traditional layout, nice flavor combos, great music selection. Ordered the Shumai and Grilled eel roll. Decent server, would recommend to any foodie passing through. Enjoy
Food is amazing, but beware late delivery service - the restaurant phone won't be answered and delivery late. However, this was the best quality Japanese delivery food I've ever had.
They're food is incredible
Yummy fresh salad with delicious homemade dressing. Fast friendly service, reasonably priced, delicious sushi.
Service was great.  Food was spectacular!  Presentation A+.
Excellent sushi. The best I've had in a very long time. A little pricey, but well worth it.
good
Looks beautiful
Very cute cozy place. Great service, delicious sushi, fast and friendly! Prices are great too.

I thought the concept was good, this place markets that it serves organic sushi very prominently. I came in for some Sushi rolls and also ordered Crab Rangoons. I had the Jackie Chan roll, it was good, but a little too heavy on the cream cheese for my taste. The Crab Rangoons were not the traditional kind I have had at Chinese restaurants, they were much more crab forward and much less cheese. Probably wouldn't order that item again.

So freakin' good. I'm obsessed with sushi in general and this place delivers in spades. All the food is organic. They deliver in a relatively timely manner but I definitely recommend going into the restaurant for the full experience. The staff is great and the sushi chefs are amazing. They make lots of different, very inventive types of maki rolls that are delicious. I had never been on such sushi adventures before going to Blue Fuji. Their chinese food is also good but their sushi shines! If you happen to make it for lunch their bento boxes are a really good value and delicious as well.  If you go, make sure to ask about any special makis they have. My mind was blown last night.
